name: Butterscotch Cake II
author: KITTEN49
summary: Use cake mix and butterscotch pudding mix to quickly and easily make this butterscotch cake recipe.
ingredients: 1 (3.4 ounce) package instant butterscotch pudding mix
¼ cup confectioners' sugar for dusting
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Grease and flour a 10 inch Bundt pan
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, milk, oil and egg whites
Beat on low speed for 30 seconds, then on medium speed for 2 minutes
Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 50 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into center of cake comes out clean
Cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack, and continue to cool completely
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar before serving
